{
  "stem": "747.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was windows, all four sides, all windows.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we could, from wherever we looked, we saw what's going on-- from the train, as they walked in, until the gate, and into the crematorium we had.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was very painful to see.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the chimney was going, day and night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, when they couldn't eliminate all these bodies so fast, then we saw the piles on-- on the yard, waiting to be burned.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many of them had to be carried out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a forest right next to the crematorium-- they called it the forbidden forest-- where they had fires.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were burning the bodies.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so one day, it was-- that was in the middle of September, it was-- the weather was still nice.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the blackberries started to grow in-- on the bushes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we knew that, if we can smuggle in some of this fruit, we can sell it for bread, what was-- was the-- really the-- one of the most precious commodity.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so, as we cleaned up the tower fast.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then the five of us started to pick the berries.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as we walked into the forest, the berries were bigger and bigger.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "All of the sudden, it was full, the dish, what we carried with us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was our only possession we had at around wall, that we had to carry under our arm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we came out from the forest, and the head of the crematorium-- the SS-- noticed us, and called us over.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And through the fence, we had to give in our fruit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And before we turned around, an SS soldier was behind us, and took us in, back to the working camp, where we-- the sleeping quarters.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
